Title: ~Z2-Z3 Long Trainer Ride with Tempo/Strength/Drills **This one by feel given all the skiing
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 15 minutes easy spinning WARMUP DRILL: Include 4 continuous sets of the following: alternating 1 min climb at 70 rpm, 1 min flat road at 90 rpm, 1 min very fast cadence over 110 rpm. Ride 5 minutes in zone 2 endurance (5-6/10) TEMPO: Ride 3 x 4 minutes tempo effort (7/10). Recover 5 minutes easy in-between. GRADUAL CLIMBS: Climb in or out of the saddle 4 x 2 minutes at 70 rpm (heavy gearing). Ride 2 minutes easy high-cadence spinning in-between. Ride 5 minutes in zone 2 endurance (5-6/10) STEEP CLIMBS: Ride 4 x 30 seconds in a heavy/big gear. Recover 90 seconds in-between. These power climbs can be seated or standing. Ride any remaining time easy to get the full volume.

Title: Z2 Long Aerobic Ride with Fast Pedal Drills
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 10-15 minutes in the Active Recovery Zone. Ride in Aerobic Zone 2. Ride in lower zone 2 as needed to ensure that you make it the entire distance. Cadence 80-105 rpm. Cool down 10 minutes in Active Recovery Zone. Include the following Fast Pedal drills to widen your cadence range and help you develop a smooth pedal stroke. Apply pressure through the entire pedal stroke, pulling through the bottom and over the top. Heartrate may climb during intervals, but do not force it up! Pedal 5 sets of 5 minute intervals on a flat or downhill terrain at 105-130+ rpm. Do your best to avoid any bouncing and rocking of your hips. Ride 5 minutes in-between the fast pedal drills at your normal cadence.

Title: Run, Tempo Fartlek Miles
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 2 miles easy. Run 1 mile in Zone 2. Then run 3 x 1 mile in the middle of zone 3 (do not go over zone 3 at all!). Run half a mile easier in betweeen, letting your heartrate come down. These are not threshold repeat miles! These are TEMPO miles, which should feel just a bit faster than your aerobic endurance pace. Cool down with 1-2 miles of easy running.

Ride 5 minute recovery between intervals. Progress the workout! Cool down 10 minutes easy.

Title: Z2 Aerobic Run + drills

Include 6 x 50 meters of running drills toward the end of your run, but before the cool-down: 1) Heel Lifts (feet come right under the hips) 2) Grapevines, alternating one foot in front of the other 3) Fast Feet: focus on landing on the balls of your feet in very short and quick steps 4) Slow Skips: drive tall and slow, alternate arms 5) Backwards running (don't trip!) 6) High Knees Cool down 5 minutes easy.

Title: Z3 Half Ironman Specific Swim
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 8 x 50, first 4 easy, last 4 build within each 50 (10 sec RI) Swim 3 x 1000. First one is at half iron pace @85% Each one gets just a little faster. Pace it so that you can pick up the pace on each one, even if it's just by a second or two. 1 minute rest interval. RECORD times in log!!! Cool down 100 easy kick.

Title: Supplemental Strength
WorkoutDescription: Do a circuit of 15-20 reps of each exercise. Do the circuit three times through. Start the first round with light weights. Use enough weight that you feel a light burn by the end of the 15-20 reps. Body-weight might be plenty for the leg exercises. Do not go to a heavy burn in your muscles. Shoulder-width Squats (body-weight or dumbell/barbell) Lat Pull Down, standing pull the bar down Tri-cep exercise (kickbacks or other) Lunges, L then R foot forward Seated Row Dead Lifts Core Exercise Can be done at home or a gym. If overly tired, this is the workout to skip in the week. Should take 25-40 minutes depending on rest in between.

Title: Z2 Run, MAF Test
WorkoutDescription: Maximum Aerobic Function (MAF) Test: how fast you run without going anaerobic at all. This test can be done on the track or the treadmill. (Track is preferable). Warmup with 15 minutes easy running. TEST: Run 3 miles continuous in the last few beats of your Aerobic Heart Rate Zone 2. Do not go over zone 2! Cool down with 5-10 minutes of easy running. Record the Total Time for three miles as well as mile splits. If done on the treadmill, get total time and average speed, if possible. Run on a 1% incline for MAF Test if done on the treadmill.
AthleteComments: *01/26/2018 Keith Kruelskie: 159 HR on 3 miles*

Title: Swim, test 100/400yd TT {2000}
WorkoutDescription: Warmup as follows 3 x 100 Freestlye (10 sec RI) 100 kick with board 100 swim with buoy 100 backstroke or breastroke Swim 6 X 50 descending to race pace (15 sec RI) Swim 100 ALL OUT for TIME Swim 200 nice and easy, take as long as you need to rest. Swim 400 ALL OUT for TIME!! Swim 3 X 200 Easy for cool down (20 sec RI) Record time in post-activity comments below.

Title: Hydration/Sweat Rate Test
WorkoutDescription: Here is the test to determine your sodium needs during training and racing. Try to do the test indoors on a big trainer with the temp set at about 75 degrees. I can also prescribe this in running format if you prefer. You must have a digital scale and feel somewhat rested to perform this test. Right before you do the test, weigh yourself with no clothes on and with whatever food you plan to eat during the test. Do not include any fluids you right drink. Use a digital scale and record the weight. Ride one hour at your 40K ITT bike race effort (minus 8 beats) or at your half ironman bike effort by power or heart rate (around Z3). If you do a warmup before, then follow number 1 before you start the test. Immediately after the hour test, dry yourself off, and then weigh yourself with no clothes on and with whatever food you weighed in with at the beginning of the test but didn’t consume. Submit the following: Weight in pounds with at least tenths included for before and after the exact amount of fluid in ounce that you consumed the weather/temperature Based on your fluid losses, a fluid plan will be developed for each race distance. Based on your lean body weight, your carbohydrate intake will also be calculated. Please answer the following What is your current body fat percentage? Guesstimate if unsure or I can recommend a cheap caliper set to buy/use off Amazon. Do you typically experience cramping or other dehydration symptoms during races? Please describe your current race nutrition protocol and comment on how it has NOT worked in the past. Include how many bottles of fluid you drink on the bike, and how many times you have needed to pee during races. Include your estimated finish time for the race/race distance you want the Race Week Fueling for.

Title: The MACH 5 MONDAY "CHECK-IN"
WorkoutDescription: The 5 in "MACH 5" refers to the five fundamental areas in life that affect athletic performance including training, health/rest, nutrition, balance, and mental/emotional. Please give me some details about the following 5 areas for today/last week: . 1) Training: how do you feel in general about your recent training and motivation? Training motivation is very high. Nice level of workouts. Feel like I could use a little more top end on running/biking but I see some of that is coming. Feeling like swimming is light. My form is there for swimming but aerobic capacity is definitely dipping. On the plus side I am feeling leaner and lighter... . 2) Health/Restoration: How many hours of sleep have you been getting the last few nights and how is the quality of your sleep? 7-8 hours most nights Are you stretching? Stretch after every workout. Foam roll maybe 2x a week. Do you have any sniffles/sore throat/cough/abnormal fatigue, etc? No Do you have any problem areas, muscularly or otherwise? Just a toenail with blood under it, and a medium size blister on my big toe. Neither of which impact my biking or running form . 3) Nutrition, how has your nutrition been the last few days? Pretty spot on except for the beer What was your morning weight? . 4) Life/Balance: How has your life-balance of work/school/family/play/stress/etc been this last week? Triathlon is my main focus outside of work, balanced well with my girlfriend and socializing! . 5) Mental/Emotional: how ya feeling in general? Anything affecting your training or racing that I should be aware of? Feeling great. A bit of FOMO about skiing on good powder days but my choice is to work towards Ironman Boulder!

Title: Run, Tempo Fartlek Miles
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 2 miles easy. Run 1 mile in Zone 2. Then run 3 x 1 mile in the middle of zone 3 (do not go over zone 3 at all!). Run half a mile easier in betweeen, letting your heartrate come down. These are not threshold repeat miles! These are TEMPO miles, which should feel just a bit faster than your aerobic endurance pace. Cool down with 1 mile of easy running.

Title: Z2 Aerobic Bike with Big Gear efforts, 3 x 10
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 15 minutes easy. Ride in Zone 2 today, pushing to the upper half of Zone 2 if feeling good. A little riding in low zone 3 during the big gear efforts is okay, but don't force it. Include 3 x 10 minutes at "big gear" efforts. Shift into a gear that puts your cadence approximately at 65-75 rpm. Focus on smooth, steady pedal strokes. Ride 10 minutes high cadence in between efforts in Z2 Cool down 10 min with high cadence zone 1 riding.

Title: Bike, Speed Drills 8 x 2
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 10 minutes easy. This is an endurance Zone 2 ride with Speed drills incorporated in it to increase cadence and build cycling economy. Do 8 rounds of the following: alternate 2 minutes seconds at very high RPM (10 rpm higher than your "normal") followed by 2 minutes at normal RPM. Heartrate can go into zone 3 some, but this is more of a fast cadence drill than it is a hard interval workout. Pedal as fast as you can without bouncing. Shift gears so effort is not hard. Ride the remainder of the ride in Zone 2. Cool down 10 minutes easy.

Title: Long Bike with Tempo Builds: 6 X 5 mins
WorkoutDescription: Tempo to threshold, building intervals Warmup 20 minutes easy spinning. Ride an hour in Aerobic Zone 2. In the latter part of the long ride, include 6 X 5 minutes with 2.5 minute recoveries. Make the first one in low zone 3, and then try to make each subsequent interval harder (and higher heartrate/power). These can get into Zone 4 by the end, but don't have to. Build throughout the workout. Ride any remaining time afterwards in zone 2. Cool down 10 minutes in easy.

Title: Z1 Bike, Recovery with handling drills
WorkoutDescription: Easy bike in Active Recovery Zone 1. Here are some drills I want you to try several times. Which ones of these can you do and not do? 1) Hands free drill.... How long can you ride without holding on. At least 1 minute? on your TT bike, yes. 2) Fast turns pedaling through... can you do 90 degree turns at speed without hitting the brakes and lightly pedaling through the turn? 3) water bottle pickup from the ground... self-explanatory 4) two-wheel bunny hop 5) fast U-turns, R and L... how do you tackle these? 6) in and outs: get your feet out and back in your shoes several times 7) shoe-less dismount and mount 8) speedy mount/flying mount... do you do these? [video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NHue50tFbF4]

Title: Z3 Bike, 2 x 15 minutes
WorkoutDescription: Warmup up 15 minutes easy. Ride 20 minutes in Z2. Ride 5 minutes easy. Ride 2 x 15 minute efforts in Z3 by power. Minimize stops and drops in intensity during this portion. Ride 5 minutes in between these two intervals. Progress the workout to finish stronger than you start. Cool down 15 minutes easy riding. Cadence: 85-95 rpm on the intervals Terrain: Flat to rolling RPE (1-10): 8 Log the 2 intervals with average HR and average non-norm power (if you have it) in the post workout comments along with your Z3 heart-rate range. We want to see an average HR in the mid to high Z3 on these.

Title: *Z2-Z3 Long Trainer Ride with Tempo/Strength/Drills
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 15 minutes easy spinning. WARMUP DRILL: Include 4 continuous sets of the following: alternating 2 min climb at 70 rpm, 2 min flat road at 90 rpm, 2 min very fast cadence over 110 rpm. Ride 10 minutes in zone 2. TEMPO: Ride 3 x 10 minutes in low to mid-zone 3. Recover 5 minutes easy in-between. DRILL: Recover with 10 minutes alternating 2 minutes Left leg, 1 minute both legs, 2 minutes right leg. GRADUAL CLIMBS: Climb 4 x 3 minutes at 70 rpm, seated. Take 3 minutes high-cadence spinning in-between. HR/power can go into low zone 3, but don't force it. Ride 10 minutes in Zone 2. STEEP CLIMBS: Ride 8 x 30 seconds in a heavy/big gear. Recover 90 seconds in-between. These power climbs can be seated or standing. HR/power not observed. Ride any remaining time in Zone 2. Cool down 10 minutes.
AthleteComments: *03/25/2018 Keith Kruelskie: Very intens*

Title: Z2 Aerobic Run + drills
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 10 minutes easy. Run Aerobic Zone 2 today. Include 6 x 50 meters of running drills toward the end of your run, but before the cool-down: 1) Heel Lifts (feet come right under the hips) 2) Grapevines, alternating one foot in front of the other 3) Fast Feet: focus on landing on the balls of your feet in very short and quick steps 4) Slow Skips: drive tall and slow, alternate arms 5) Backwards running (don't trip!) 6) High Knees Cool down 5 minutes easy.

Title: Z2 Aerobic Bike with Big Gear efforts, 3 x 10
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 15 minutes easy. Ride in Zone 2 today, pushing to the upper half of Zone 2 if feeling good. A little riding in low zone 3 during the big gear efforts is okay, but don't force it. Include 3 x 10 minutes at "big gear" efforts. Shift into a gear that puts your cadence approximately at 65-75 rpm. Focus on smooth, steady pedal strokes. Ride 10 minutes high cadence in between efforts in Z2 Cool down 10 min with high cadence zone 1 riding.

Title: Z2 Run, MAF Test
WorkoutDescription: Maximum Aerobic Function (MAF) Test: how fast you run without going anaerobic at all. This test can be done on the track or the treadmill. (Track is preferable). Warmup with 15 minutes easy running. TEST: Run 3 miles continuous in the last few beats of your Aerobic Heart Rate Zone 2. Do not go over zone 2! Cool down with 5-10 minutes of easy running. Record the Total Time for three miles as well as mile splits. If done on the treadmill, get total time and average speed, if possible. Run on a 1% incline for MAF Test if done on the treadmill.
AthleteComments: *03/30/2018 Keith Kruelskie: 3 miles at 6:46/mile*

Title: Quality long bike: LT/V02 Max Mixed workout, 6s
WorkoutDescription: Lactate Threshold and V02 Max Mixed Workout. Warmup 15 minutes easy. Ride 60 minutes in Aerobic Zone 2, then do 4 X 30 second pickups with 1 minute recovery between each. Ride a few minutes easy, stop and stretch if feeling tight. Main Workout: Bike 6 x 30 seconds very hard at RPE 9 without worrying about heartrate. Take 1 minute between intervals. Take 2 minutes easy after all 5. Bike 6 X 1 minute working up to zone 4+ Take 1 minute between intervals. Take two minutes easy after all 5. Bike 3 X 3 minutes above LT Take two minutes easy between and after. Bike a 6 min threshold interval around your LT. Ride any remaining time in zones 1-2 Cool down with 10 minutes easy spinning.

Title: 3/20 Anaerobic/Aerobic LT Test
WorkoutDescription: Warmup: 20 minutes easy in Zones 1 and 2. Ride 3 X 1 minute fast pedaling at 100rpm to get things moving. Ride 5 minutes easy. Perform the test on a relatively flat road or on an indoor trainer. Main Set: Ride 3 minutes ALL OUT BEST EFFORT. Ride easy 10 minutes. Rice 20 min Time Trial BEST EFFORT. Make both of these tests as steady as possible. Do not go too hard at the beginning so that you can't hold a steady effort. Ride any remaining time easy. Cool Down 110 minutes. Record your average heartrate and average normalized power (if using a powermeter) for both the 3 minute and 20 minute efforts.

Title: Z1/low Z2 Easy Endurance Run + Drills
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 10 minutes easy. Run EASY endurance pace in Z1 to low zone 2. Do not force pace or intensity today. Include 6 x 50 meters of running drills toward the end of your run, but before the cooldown: 1) Butt Kicks 2) Side Shuffles--alternating one foot in front of the other) 3) Fast Feet--focus on landing on the balls of your feet in very short and quick steps 4) Skips--drive tall and slow, alternate arms 5) Backwards running 6) High Knees Cool down 5 minutes in the Active Recovery Zone. Cadence is 90+ steps per minute.

Title: Supplemental Strength (1 round)
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 5 minutes easy cardio. Repeat 1 time through circuit or do 3 repeats of each exercise before moving on to the next one (circuit is preferable). Take 30-60 seconds rest between each. Use a weight that produces a light burn by the end of the reps. 15 squats with weights 15 seated row 15 lat pull down 15 hack squats 15 dips/tricep kick backs 15 pushups 15 lunges with light weights 15 bicep curls 15 dead lifts with heavy weight 3 minutes core work (planks, ball, etc)

Title: Bike, Endurance + drill (Spin-ups + Single Leg)
WorkoutDescription: Warmup up 10 minutes easy spinning. Ride endurance pace in the Aerobic Zone 2. Some riding in Zone 3 during drills is fine. Include pedaling drill: Do the following 3 times: 10 seconds of high rpm, 10 seconds higher, 10 seconds max rpm and then recover for 60 seconds. Then do this 3 times: 30 seconds left followed by 30 seconds right-leg dominant pedaling (other leg soft-pedals). Repeat both of these drills 4-5 times. Done in small chain ring or on spin bike. Cool down 5-10 minutes easy spinning

Title: Z2 Aerobic Run + Drill Set B

Title: Z2 Aerobic Bike with 6 x 2 min hard intervals
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 10 minutes easy spinning. Then ride for 5 minutes alternating "10 seconds on/10 seconds off." On means hard, off means soft-pedaling. Ride mostly today in Aerobic Endurance Zone 2. Include 6 x 2 minutes very hard (threshold to V02max) efforts, preferably on an uphill, big-gear or into a headwind. These should go into your upper HR zones. Take long recoveries. Cool down 10 minutes easy.

Title: Z3/Z2 Brick Run with 10 minutes of speedwork

Title: Long Z2 Aerobic Bike with Big Gear efforts, 3 x 15 min...can you bike long today or tomorrow?
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 15 minutes easy. Ride in Zone 2 today, pushing to the upper half of Zone 2 if feeling good. Include 3 x 15 minutes at "big gear" efforts. Shift into a gear that puts your cadence approximately at 70 rpm. Focus on a smooth, steady pedal strokes. Ride into zone 3 if feeling good. Ride 10 minutes high cadence in between efforts. Cool down 10 min with high cadence zone 1 riding.

Title: Bike, Z2 MAF Test for Power Average on trainer
WorkoutDescription: Maximum Aerobic Function (MAF) Test to test aerobic power based off of HR Aerobic zone. Warmup 15 minutes easy. Throw in some pickups to get the HR/power up a bit. Pick a course that is relatively flat and can be repeated in the future. Ride 10 miles (or 30 minutes) in the top 4 beats of your Aerobic Heart Rate Zone 2. If you go over Zone 2, slow down so that you come back into Zone 2 (otherwise the test is invalid). Record the following for the test: 1) Average HR 2) Average Power 3) Average Cadence 4) Average Speed 5) How you felt Ride the rest of the ride in Aerobic Zone 2. Cool down 10 minutes easy.

Ride 2.5 minutes easy recovery between intervals. Cool down 10 minutes in easy.

Title: Swim, 400s Hard/Steady {5000}
WorkoutDescription: 500 free 6x100 alt kick (side/back kick, 50 hard 50 easy) / drill (personal weakness) 6x200 done as steady 10s rest, mod-hard 15s rest, hard 30s rest - repeat 100 easy 6x100 alt IM steady on 20s rest / free, hard, 5s rest (free to IM transition will be tough) 100 easy 5x400 done as #1 - 300 hard, 100 steady - 30s rest #2 - 200 hard, 200 steady - 20s rest #3 - 100 hard, 300 steady - 10s rest #4 - 100 hard, 300 steady - 20s rest #5 - 400 easy Note that the pace of the second part of the 400 is steady, not easy. The goal is to slowly reduce the oxygen debt while swimming at a steady pace. Should take at least 100m before you feel comfortable. The first 50 will feel uncomfortable, we want you to get used to that sensation. 100 easy stroke for cool down

Title: Long Ride with 3/20 Anaerobic/Aerobic LT Test
WorkoutDescription: Warmup: 20 minutes easy in Zones 1 and 2. Ride 3 X 1 minute fast pedaling at 100rpm to get things moving. Ride 5 minutes easy. Perform the test on a relatively flat road or on an indoor trainer. Main Set: Ride 3 minutes ALL OUT BEST EFFORT. Ride easy 10 minutes. Rice 20 min Time Trial BEST EFFORT. Make both of these tests as steady as possible. Do not go too hard at the beginning so that you can't hold a steady effort. Ride any remaining time in Zones 1 and 2. Cool down 10 minutes esy Record your average heartrate and average normalized power (if using a powermeter) for both the 3 minute and 20 minute efforts. Hit lap buttons on the start and end of both the 3 and 20 minute segments.

Title: Z2 Long Ride with 3 x 20 minutes at top low zone 3 for power avergage
WorkoutDescription: Warmup up 15 minutes easy. Ride the majority of the ride at endurance pace in the Aerobic Zone 2. Include 3 x 20 minute continuous segments where you push to HR mid zone 3 and get the non-norm power average. Take 10 minutes easier riding between these two intervals. Ride any remaining time in Z1/low Z2. Cool down 10 minutes easy. Log in the post workout comments 1) the avegage HR, average non-norm power for each 20 minute interval 2) your current Z2 HR and power zone. Cadence: 80-105 rpm, with cadence mostly in the upper 80s to 90s. Terrain: Flat to rolling RPE (1-10): 6-7
AthleteComments: *08/18/2018 Keith Kruelskie: 275W for the 20min intervals*

Title: Long Z2 Bike with Big Gear long and short efforts
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 15 minutes easy. Ride in Zone 2 today, pushing to the upper half of Zone 2 if feeling good. Include 3 x 10 minutes at "big gear" efforts. Shift into a gear that puts your cadence approximately at 70 rpm. Focus on a smooth, steady pedal strokes. Ride into zone 3 if feeling good. Ride 10 minutes high cadence in between efforts. Then ride 3 x 3 minutes big gear trying to push into Z3. Ride 5 minutes high cadence between each. 10 minutes high after the set Then ride 6 x 1 minute out-of the-saddle big gear climbs in Z2/Z3. Take 2 minutes easy spinning between these. Ride any remaining time in Z2 Cool down 10 min with high cadence zone 1 riding.

Title: Bike Quality, 3-blocks
WorkoutDescription: Warm-up 10 mins easy spinning followed by 3 x 30 secs in an easy gear at high cadence with 30 secs recovery. Then spin 5 mins easy spinning. Main set 3 x 10 min blocks with 5 mins easy spinning after each one: Block 1: Ride 10 minutes alternating 45 secs hard with15 seconds easy. Use a big gear that puts you around 70 rpms on the hard and don't shift during the easy part... just soft pedal in that big gear. HR/power should go up into Z3 (or 85% by feel) Block 2: Ride 10 minutes alternating 20 secs hard with10 seconds easy. Use a big gear that puts you around 70 rpms on the hard and don't shift during the easy part... just soft pedal in that big gear. HR/power should go up into Z3 (or 85% by feel) Block 3: Ride 10 minutes alternating 20 secs hard out of the saddle and 40 seconds easy in the saddle (shift to easier gear on the 40 easy). Progress across the 10 minutes to make them harder effort as you go. Cool-down any remaining time.

Title: 100 Mile IRONMAN Prep Ride INCLUDING "Climbs"
WorkoutDescription: This 100 mile ride should be done on 4 x 25-mile loops/trainer segments. Ride the first 25 at an easy pace in Z1 to low Z2 (below IM effort). This should feel controlled. If you’re puffing, you’re going too hard! Focus on nutrition. Ride the second 25 focused on your bike position. Ride at your target IM race effort. Stay strictly in aero. Throw in some climbs! Keep your upper body still. Concentrate on efficient, smooth, strong riding. Ride the third 25 miles below your target IM race effort in mid Z2. This should be a marginal drop in effort and not a significant reduction from applying yourself to gentle spinning. Keep the momentum of the ride going. Focus on nutrition and form. Ride the final lap at an effort level that’s greater than your IM bike target effort in low Z3.

Main set: Swim 2 X 400, 2 X 300, 2 X 200, 2 X 100. Use a base interval that gives you about 15 seconds rest between everything. PACE and intensity are aerobic. Kick 6 x 50 Freestyle with kickboard. Title: Swim, 400s Hard/Steady {5000}
WorkoutDescription: 500 free 6x100 alt kick (side/back kick, 50 hard 50 easy) / drill (personal weakness) 6x200 done as steady 10s rest, mod-hard 15s rest, hard 30s rest - repeat 100 easy 6x100 alt IM steady on 20s rest / free, hard, 5s rest (free to IM transition will be tough) 100 easy 5x400 done as #1 - 300 hard, 100 steady - 30s rest #2 - 200 hard, 200 steady - 20s rest #3 - 100 hard, 300 steady - 10s rest #4 - 100 hard, 300 steady - 20s rest #5 - 400 easy Note that the pace of the second part of the 400 is steady, not easy. The goal is to slowly reduce the oxygen debt while swimming at a steady pace. Should take at least 100m before you feel comfortable. The first 50 will feel uncomfortable, we want you to get used to that sensation. 100 easy stroke for cool down

WorkoutDescription: Maximum Aerobic Function (MAF) Test: how fast you run without going anaerobic at all. This test can be done on the track or the treadmill. (Track is preferable). Warmup with 15 minutes easy running. TEST: Run 4 miles continuous in the last few beats of your Aerobic Heart Rate Zone 2. Do not go over zone 2! Cool down with 5-10 minutes of easy running. Record the Total Time for 4 miles as well as mile splits. If done on the treadmill, get total time and average speed, if possible. Run on a 1% incline for MAF Test if done on the treadmill.

Title: On/Offs 6 sec sprint
WorkoutDescription: Ride in Zone 1-2. Keep your cadence over 85 rpm on the flats. Perform 2 x 5 minute On/Off intervals. Start the interval with a 6 second sprint at 95%, recover for 24 seconds with easy spinning, then sprint again for 6 seconds. Repeat for the interval duration. Gear: 53 x 15-16. Alternate: seated sprint / out-the-saddle sprint. Recover for 5 min+ between intervals. *Optional rest day (then do on/offs on one of the weekend rides)

Title: The MACH 5 MONDAY "CHECK-IN"
WorkoutDescription: The 5 in "MACH 5" refers to the five fundamental areas in life that affect athletic performance including training, health/rest, nutrition, balance, and mental/emotional. Please give me some details about the following 5 areas for today/last week: . 1) Training: how do you feel in general about your recent training and motivation? . 2) Health/Restoration: How many hours of sleep have you been getting the last few nights and how is the quality of your sleep? Are you stretching? Do you have any sniffles/sore throat/cough/abnormal fatigue, etc? Do you have any problem areas, muscularly or otherwise? . 3) Nutrition, how has your nutrition been the last few days? What was your morning weight? . 4) Life/Balance: How has your life-balance of work/school/family/play/stress/etc been this last week? . 5) Mental/Emotional: how ya feeling in general? Anything affecting your training or racing that I should be aware of?

Title: Run, Tempo Fartlek: 30/60/2min & Form Sprints
WorkoutDescription: Tempo Fartlek (alternating speeds) Run. Warmup 10 minutes easy. Run 4 x 30 seconds at 5K effort with 30 seconds easy jog in-between. Run 2 minutes easy. Run 4 x 60 seconds at 5K effort with 60 seconds easy jog in-between. Run 2 minutes easy. Run 2 x 2 minutes at 5K effort with 2 minutes easy jog in-between. Run 2 minutes easy. Do 4 x ~15 seconds "Form Sprints" where you run as fast as you can with perfect form. Do not run long enough where these really tire you. Get up to your max, run some strides at max speed, then slow it down. Run easy 45 seconds in-between. Run any remaining time/mileage in zone 1/2. Cool down 5 minutes easy.

Title: Z2 Aerobic Run before or after the bike
WorkoutDescription: Warmup and cooldown as needed. Endurance run before or after bike session. All zone 2.

Title: Z2-Z3 Long Trainer Ride with Tempo/Strength/Drills
WorkoutDescription: This workout can be done on the trainer or outside (other than the 1 legged drills... don't do those outside!) Warmup 15 minutes easy spinning. WARMUP DRILL: Include 4 continuous sets of the following: alternating 2 min climb at 70 rpm, 2 min flat road at 90 rpm, 2 min very fast cadence over 110 rpm. Ride 10 minutes in zone 2. TEMPO: Ride 3 x 10 minutes in low to mid-zone 3. Recover 5 minutes easy in-between. DRILL: Recover with 10 minutes alternating 2 minutes Left leg, 1 minute both legs, 2 minutes right leg. GRADUAL CLIMBS: Climb 4 x 3 minutes at 70 rpm, seated. Take 3 minutes high-cadence spinning in-between. HR/power can go into low zone 3, but don't force it. Ride 10 minutes in Zone 2. STEEP CLIMBS: Ride 8 x 30 seconds in a heavy/big gear. Recover 90 seconds in-between. These power climbs can be seated or standing. HR/power not observed. Ride any remaining time in Zone 2. Cool down 10 minutes.
